- 'shining brightly' refers to having the highest average rating;
- 'most highly regarded' indicates the course with the highest average rating.

- Courses with more than 10 enrollments are considered popular or well-attended;
- A total material cost of less than 200 is considered affordable;
- Courses taught by more than one instructor might benefit from diverse perspectives.

- 'Sophomore' refers to students in their second year of college;
- 'Average rating' is calculated by averaging the ratings given by students for each course;
- 'Total enrollment' is the number of students enrolled in each class.

sql:
SELECT class_code, delivery_method, enrollment_limit
FROM class_schedules
ORDER BY enrollment_limit DESC;

